defaultWritten evidence submitted by the Anaerobic Digestion and Biogas Association (HOT47)default&#xa0;defaultThe Anaerobic Digestion and Biogas Association (ADBA) is the trade association that represents the range of interests and matters related to the anaerobic digestion of organic materials (“AD”) across the 
defaultUK
default. The organisation has over 
default350
default members from acros
defaults the AD industry, including farmers, local authorities, waste management companies, supermarkets, food processors, plant operators, energy and water companies, equipment manufacturers and suppliers, consultants, financiers and supporting service companies
